194
00:17:32,199 --> 00:17:33,569
So I came out first.

195
00:17:41,509 --> 00:17:42,449
If I had known...

196
00:17:42,449 --> 00:17:45,079
I don't want to talk about that here.

197
00:17:52,189 --> 00:17:53,289
Here?

198
00:17:53,889 --> 00:17:55,789
The rooftop?

199
00:17:57,099 --> 00:17:59,329
Or the building your father lives in?

200
00:18:06,599 --> 00:18:07,599
Oh, okay.

201
00:18:08,239 --> 00:18:09,769
I get what you're saying.

202
00:18:13,079 --> 00:18:15,579
Setting boundaries is a good thing.

203
00:18:29,329 --> 00:18:30,629
Want something to eat?

204
00:18:36,669 --> 00:18:37,969
Want some milk?

205
00:18:38,369 --> 00:18:39,369
Milk...

206
00:18:40,539 --> 00:18:41,439
Do you not like milk?

207
00:18:41,439 --> 00:18:43,509
But I only have milk.

208
00:19:02,629 --> 00:19:04,229
We were supposed to die together

209
00:19:04,229 --> 00:19:06,029
if we met by chance next time.

210
00:19:06,799 --> 00:19:08,969
But we've met too quickly.

211
00:19:12,569 --> 00:19:15,539
We can't die while drinking milk.

212
00:19:17,509 --> 00:19:19,879
Do you usually speak so rashly?

213
00:19:21,539 --> 00:19:22,609
What do you mean?

214
00:19:23,479 --> 00:19:26,119
Things like, "Let's die together."

215
00:19:28,849 --> 00:19:29,949
No.

216
00:19:33,159 --> 00:19:34,259
Not at all.

217
00:19:35,889 --> 00:19:37,429
Then why did you?

218
00:19:40,999 --> 00:19:42,099
Well.

219
00:19:43,369 --> 00:19:45,499
I don't know why I said that.

220
00:20:00,619 --> 00:20:03,049
I can guess what kind of
instant noodles you got.

221
00:20:04,889 --> 00:20:05,989
Instant noodles?

222
00:20:06,689 --> 00:20:08,959
You always eat the same thing.

223
00:20:09,589 --> 00:20:10,759
Korean beef instant noodles.

224
00:20:12,059 --> 00:20:12,929
Huh?

225
00:20:14,329 --> 00:20:15,599
Wow.

226
00:20:16,829 --> 00:20:18,169
How did you know?

227
00:20:19,799 --> 00:20:21,599
I just knew.

228
00:20:23,069 --> 00:20:24,369
Wow.

229
00:20:25,779 --> 00:20:29,149
It's good you have a favorite.

230
00:20:31,749 --> 00:20:33,019
You don't have

231
00:20:33,319 --> 00:20:34,379
a favorite?

232
00:20:35,449 --> 00:20:36,989
I don't think so.

233
00:20:37,649 --> 00:20:39,259
I did long ago.

234
00:20:40,689 --> 00:20:43,489
I had likes and dislikes.

235
00:20:44,029 --> 00:20:46,759
I had easy issues and hard issues.

236
00:20:48,969 --> 00:20:51,329
But at some point,

237
00:20:51,599 --> 00:20:53,199
everything became the same.

238
00:20:55,169 --> 00:20:57,809
I don't like it nor do I dislike it.

239
00:20:58,469 --> 00:21:00,479
It's neither easy nor hard.

240
00:21:10,549 --> 00:21:12,319
Last year, for a brief moment,

241
00:21:13,789 --> 00:21:15,689
I had a baby.

242
00:21:17,529 --> 00:21:20,299
In my belly for about 5 months.

243
00:21:23,799 --> 00:21:25,169
I was so busy then

244
00:21:25,169 --> 00:21:27,439
that I didn't have time to be happy.

245
00:21:29,339 --> 00:21:31,009
Then I lost it.

246
00:21:31,909 --> 00:21:34,039
Even before I could celebrate.

247
00:21:43,589 --> 00:21:45,319
<i>Because of you,</i>

248
00:21:46,359 --> 00:21:47,859
<i>I lost my job.</i>

249
00:21:48,819 --> 00:21:50,159
<i>I lost my child.</i>

250
00:21:51,189 --> 00:21:52,699
<i>And I lost myself.</i>

251
00:21:52,999 --> 00:21:54,559
<i>But you...</i>

252
00:22:02,639 --> 00:22:05,939
I was physically exhausted
and constantly crying.

253
00:22:07,139 --> 00:22:08,839
But on the inside,

254
00:22:10,749 --> 00:22:13,049
strangely, it was all the same.

255
00:22:14,879 --> 00:22:17,279
There was nothing of mine inside me.

256
00:22:18,249 --> 00:22:19,989
I didn't know why I was sad

257
00:22:19,989 --> 00:22:22,019
or why I was angry.

258
00:22:22,959 --> 00:22:24,729
I was just embarrassed.

259
00:22:31,199 --> 00:22:33,569
When you don't have a favorite,

260
00:22:35,399 --> 00:22:37,939
it's not just that favorite thing
that disappears,

261
00:22:40,009 --> 00:22:42,279
but everything disappears all together.

262
00:22:47,549 --> 00:22:49,689
That song from earlier.

263
00:22:49,819 --> 00:22:52,049
Can I listen to it again now?

264
00:23:29,689 --> 00:23:31,359
Is this a song you like?

265
00:23:33,659 --> 00:23:34,829
No.

266
00:23:36,699 --> 00:23:38,469
It's a song I know.

267
00:23:42,639 --> 00:23:43,639
But

268
00:23:45,479 --> 00:23:47,239
listening to it like this,

269
00:23:48,879 --> 00:23:50,079
I see it's good.

270
00:25:28,309 --> 00:25:29,679
What were you listening to?

271
00:25:31,109 --> 00:25:32,579
Oh, just

272
00:25:32,579 --> 00:25:33,949
a song.

273
00:25:50,999 --> 00:25:52,099
But

274
00:25:53,099 --> 00:25:55,139
can you be out here when you're sick?

275
00:25:55,439 --> 00:25:56,839
You didn't even make it to work.

276
00:25:56,839 --> 00:25:57,839
Oh.

277
00:25:58,509 --> 00:26:01,009
I got better as night fell.

278
