371
00:36:26,969 --> 00:36:28,669
It doesn't seem like the club.

372
00:36:29,739 --> 00:36:30,839
Nowhere.

373
00:36:32,569 --> 00:36:33,639
I'm outside.

374
00:36:34,239 --> 00:36:35,239
You?

375
00:36:36,039 --> 00:36:38,079
<i>At home.</i>

376
00:36:40,879 --> 00:36:43,419
What are you doing at home already?

377
00:36:43,419 --> 00:36:45,089
You're young.

378
00:36:47,959 --> 00:36:48,959
Hey.

379
00:36:49,759 --> 00:36:51,089
<i>What happened with that woman?</i>

380
00:36:52,529 --> 00:36:53,829
<i>How far did you get?</i>

381
00:36:54,499 --> 00:36:55,859
What do you mean?

382
00:36:55,859 --> 00:36:57,169
What woman?

383
00:36:57,269 --> 00:36:59,029
Oh, wow.

384
00:36:59,129 --> 00:37:01,639
Your voice is so moist.

385
00:37:01,969 --> 00:37:03,209
You must've met her.

386
00:37:07,639 --> 00:37:08,809
<i>Did you sleep with her?</i>

387
00:37:20,619 --> 00:37:21,719
Hello?

388
00:37:23,689 --> 00:37:25,229
What are you talking about?

389
00:37:25,859 --> 00:37:28,559
Don't act modest.

390
00:37:29,299 --> 00:37:30,669
You haven't met her yet?

391
00:37:32,029 --> 00:37:33,269
<i>No, I haven't.</i>

392
00:37:37,739 --> 00:37:38,909
Really?

393
00:37:39,969 --> 00:37:40,939
<i>Yes.</i>

394
00:37:43,379 --> 00:37:45,349
Is that so?

395
00:37:46,879 --> 00:37:49,749
<i>Meeting someone isn't that easy.</i>

396
00:37:49,749 --> 00:37:51,589
We were total strangers a few days ago.

397
00:37:52,719 --> 00:37:54,619
I texted her, but she's not replying.

398
00:37:55,159 --> 00:37:56,259
<i>I see.</i>

399
00:37:58,629 --> 00:38:01,499
I thought she'd be easy
because she's ordinary.

400
00:38:01,699 --> 00:38:03,729
<i>- (Band-aid)
- I guess she isn't.</i>

401
00:38:04,299 --> 00:38:06,429
You can't tell a book by its cover.

402
00:38:08,069 --> 00:38:11,609
<i>I really want to know
what kind of person she is.</i>

403
00:38:12,039 --> 00:38:13,639
I'll text you when she calls.

404
00:38:30,889 --> 00:38:32,189
<i>Your blouse.</i>

405
00:38:34,059 --> 00:38:37,099
<i>There's a button undone in the back.</i>

406
00:38:37,969 --> 00:38:40,139
<i>I was wondering if it's okay.</i>

407
00:38:43,869 --> 00:38:44,989
<i>If, by chance,</i>

408
00:38:46,069 --> 00:38:47,709
<i>we meet again coincidentally,</i>

409
00:38:48,509 --> 00:38:50,809
<i>but not like today,</i>

410
00:38:52,079 --> 00:38:53,949
<i>do you want to die with me?</i>

411
00:39:23,209 --> 00:39:25,109
Are you asleep, Dad?

412
00:39:26,179 --> 00:39:27,749
Of course I am.

413
00:39:30,249 --> 00:39:32,089
No, you're not.

414
00:39:32,949 --> 00:39:35,589
Go to sleep. You must be tired.

415
00:39:35,589 --> 00:39:39,229
Okay. Good night.

416
00:39:39,229 --> 00:39:40,459
Good night.

417
00:39:47,299 --> 00:39:50,309
It's cold. You dressed too lightly.

418
00:39:50,809 --> 00:39:53,139
It was warm during the day.

419
00:39:53,269 --> 00:39:55,739
It got cold all of a sudden at night.

420
00:39:56,579 --> 00:39:58,709
What time did you get in?

421
00:40:00,419 --> 00:40:02,519
Until that late,

422
00:40:05,349 --> 00:40:06,959
were you

423
00:40:08,989 --> 00:40:11,259
working at your office?

424
00:40:13,029 --> 00:40:14,259
No.

425
00:40:15,699 --> 00:40:18,099
I was out, meeting people.

426
00:40:18,799 --> 00:40:20,239
People?

427
00:40:20,699 --> 00:40:22,299
Yes, people.

428
00:40:23,269 --> 00:40:24,609
Several people.

429
00:40:27,309 --> 00:40:29,079
That must've been hard.

430
00:40:30,179 --> 00:40:31,249
Yeah.

431
00:40:32,149 --> 00:40:34,279
Meeting people

432
00:40:35,249 --> 00:40:37,119
is the hardest thing.

433
00:40:38,719 --> 00:40:40,259
But today

434
00:40:41,589 --> 00:40:43,259
was alright.

435
00:40:57,769 --> 00:40:59,369
Are you sleeping, Dad?

436
00:41:00,279 --> 00:41:01,679
No.

437
00:41:03,809 --> 00:41:05,179
Dad.

438
00:41:06,309 --> 00:41:07,379
Yeah?

439
00:41:08,849 --> 00:41:11,049
Has this ever happened to you?

440
00:41:13,419 --> 00:41:15,889
Your heart pounds so much

441
00:41:17,829 --> 00:41:19,229
that your clothes move

442
00:41:21,799 --> 00:41:24,399
like this? Like this?

443
00:41:24,999 --> 00:41:26,939
Along with your heart?

444
00:41:28,699 --> 00:41:31,369
Your heart pounds inside you.

445
00:41:33,339 --> 00:41:35,879
Why would the clothes you wear move?

446
00:41:36,909 --> 00:41:38,109
I know, right?

447
00:41:38,109 --> 00:41:39,209
But

448
00:41:40,819 --> 00:41:42,749
it really moved.

449
00:41:45,149 --> 00:41:47,319
It's not like I was running.

450
00:41:48,459 --> 00:41:50,489
I wasn't startled.

451
00:41:52,289 --> 00:41:54,499
I wasn't even that happy.

452
00:41:55,929 --> 00:41:57,669
That's puzzling.

453
00:41:58,199 --> 00:41:59,899
It is, right?

454
00:42:01,399 --> 00:42:02,569
Then

455
00:42:03,809 --> 00:42:06,209
isn't that person sick?

456
00:42:07,409 --> 00:42:09,539
No, they're not.

457
00:42:11,709 --> 00:42:12,879
What about you?

458
00:42:13,309 --> 00:42:14,319
Huh?

459
00:42:15,779 --> 00:42:17,919
Are you okay?

460
00:42:19,289 --> 00:42:21,189
You aren't sick?

461
00:42:22,659 --> 00:42:24,359
No, I'm not.

462
00:42:25,689 --> 00:42:26,759
Okay.

463
00:42:28,299 --> 00:42:30,569
If you aren't sick, then that's great.

464
00:42:32,699 --> 00:42:34,119
If you aren't sick,

465
00:42:35,039 --> 00:42:37,309
then you'll live.

466
00:42:39,339 --> 00:42:40,309
Yes.

467
00:42:41,509 --> 00:42:43,109
Good night.

468
00:42:44,709 --> 00:42:45,809
Good night.

469
00:43:08,499 --> 00:43:10,839
<i>(No hope whatsoever)</i>

470
00:43:15,979 --> 00:43:18,249
<i>(Death Certificate)</i>

471
00:44:16,709 --> 00:44:18,139
<i>Hello.</i>

472
00:44:19,419 --> 00:44:20,999
<i>It's been a long time.</i>

473
00:44:32,329 --> 00:44:34,180
<i>(Hello... It's been a long time.)</i>

474
00:44:34,189 --> 00:44:38,159
<i>More than anything,
I was glad that you seemed</i>

475
00:44:38,329 --> 00:44:39,689
<i>to be doing well.</i>

476
00:44:47,739 --> 00:44:50,609
<i>I don't know for sure,</i>

477
00:44:51,009 --> 00:44:52,339
<i>but as I live,</i>

478
00:44:52,569 --> 00:44:58,109
<i>I think I'll encounter some good days.</i>

479
00:45:03,279 --> 00:45:05,019
<i>Like when you walk after running.</i>

480
00:45:06,019 --> 00:45:07,959
<i>Like when you sit after walking.</i>

481
00:45:11,989 --> 00:45:14,859
<i>Even if it's peace
that won't last for long,</i>

482
00:45:16,599 --> 00:45:20,029
<i>there will be days that I can call good</i>

483
00:45:21,439 --> 00:45:23,339
<i>because there's rest.</i>

484
00:45:24,939 --> 00:45:26,539
<i>That's what I believe.</i>

485
00:45:35,749 --> 00:45:37,549
<i>Like walking after resting.</i>

486
00:45:40,019 --> 00:45:42,489
<i>Like running again after walking.</i>

487
00:45:47,429 --> 00:45:51,429
<i>Like rain turning into snow
and piling up.</i>

488
00:45:55,369 --> 00:45:57,539
<i>The post you sent a photo of</i>

489
00:45:57,709 --> 00:45:59,469
<i>was not written by me.</i>

490
00:46:00,709 --> 00:46:03,009
<i>The account is not mine.</i>

491
00:46:03,209 --> 00:46:07,249
<i>It cannot be me anymore.</i>

492
00:46:54,159 --> 00:46:55,999
You're coming from Father's house?

493
00:46:56,529 --> 00:46:57,629
Yes.

494
00:47:28,159 --> 00:47:30,429
You must be devastated.

495
00:47:31,529 --> 00:47:32,629
Oh, dear.

496
00:47:32,629 --> 00:47:34,969
How did you come such a long way?

497
00:47:34,969 --> 00:47:36,839
We took the express bus.

498
00:47:38,539 --> 00:47:42,309
You must be so sad and hurt.

499
00:47:42,979 --> 00:47:45,279
Honey, you should say hello.

500
00:47:45,279 --> 00:47:46,809
What? Oh.

501
00:47:46,809 --> 00:47:47,809
Huh?

502
00:47:49,679 --> 00:47:53,249
My parents owed him a lot
when he was alive.

503
00:47:53,249 --> 00:47:55,489
- I see.
- Yes, they owed him a lot.

504
00:47:55,489 --> 00:47:57,759
Yes, my late future father-in-law

505
00:47:57,759 --> 00:48:00,129
spoke a lot about your parents.

506
00:48:00,129 --> 00:48:02,629
My parents wanted me
to tell you they're grateful.

507
00:48:02,629 --> 00:48:03,629
Right.

508
00:48:03,799 --> 00:48:05,799
You haven't eaten yet, right?

509
00:48:06,199 --> 00:48:07,199
You must eat.

510
00:48:07,199 --> 00:48:08,139
Yes.

511
00:48:08,139 --> 00:48:09,799
Yes, I heard.

512
00:48:13,239 --> 00:48:15,809
- Welcome.
- You must be so sad.

513
00:48:15,809 --> 00:48:16,839
I'm okay.

514
00:48:17,609 --> 00:48:19,709
This is my husband-to-be.

515
00:48:20,179 --> 00:48:21,519
He's handsome.

516
00:48:21,519 --> 00:48:22,879
A spring wedding...

517
00:48:22,879 --> 00:48:25,219
You had to cancel your wedding

518
00:48:25,219 --> 00:48:27,019
because your father died.

519
00:48:27,019 --> 00:48:29,019
I'm so sorry.

520
00:48:39,399 --> 00:48:40,799
So to summarize, it's this.

521
00:48:40,969 --> 00:48:42,939
The king fell in love with a woman.

522
00:48:42,939 --> 00:48:44,569
But she was married.

523
00:48:44,569 --> 00:48:47,209
So he sent her husband
to war and killed him.

524
00:48:48,239 --> 00:48:50,909
He didn't kill him himself.

525
00:48:50,909 --> 00:48:51,909
I know.

526
00:48:52,249 --> 00:48:53,879
He sent him, wanting him to be killed.

527
00:48:53,879 --> 00:48:55,249
And he was killed.

528
00:48:56,649 --> 00:48:58,049
And the two lived happily ever after.

529
00:48:59,219 --> 00:49:00,249
That's it?

530
00:49:00,249 --> 00:49:02,419
In a nutshell.

531
00:49:03,119 --> 00:49:04,729
That's not what's important.

532
00:49:05,029 --> 00:49:07,729
The king and the woman's husband

533
00:49:08,099 --> 00:49:09,829
