538
00:49:19,409 --> 00:49:21,139
Why are you bringing up your mom?

539
00:49:21,139 --> 00:49:23,039
The context is similar.

540
00:49:23,809 --> 00:49:25,579
No way.

541
00:49:29,479 --> 00:49:32,319
When did you become
friends with Gang-jae?

542
00:49:32,649 --> 00:49:33,689
Me?

543
00:49:33,689 --> 00:49:34,689
Yes.

544
00:49:35,789 --> 00:49:37,229
Let me see.

545
00:49:37,729 --> 00:49:40,559
I've known him for 5-6 years.

546
00:49:41,029 --> 00:49:43,199
The first time we met...

547
00:49:44,099 --> 00:49:48,039
There's a street famous
for street casting.

548
00:49:49,199 --> 00:49:51,869
It turned out to be a false rumor,

549
00:49:53,209 --> 00:49:55,609
but we met on that street.

550
00:49:56,809 --> 00:49:58,479
We became friends a year later.

551
00:49:58,809 --> 00:49:59,849
Oh.

552
00:49:59,869 --> 00:50:01,259
Well...

553
00:50:01,279 --> 00:50:02,979
When I was kicked out of
the trainee dorm,

554
00:50:02,979 --> 00:50:04,749
he let me crash at his place.

555
00:50:06,149 --> 00:50:09,089
He... let you sleep at his place?

556
00:50:09,089 --> 00:50:10,019
Yes.

557
00:50:10,529 --> 00:50:12,359
A lot. He let me in a lot.

558
00:50:18,869 --> 00:50:21,399
I was going to go to Seoul
without interfering,

559
00:50:21,399 --> 00:50:23,299
but I can't keep listening to this.

560
00:50:24,169 --> 00:50:25,339
What do you mean "a lot"?

561
00:50:25,339 --> 00:50:26,769
I let you crash only twice.

562
00:50:27,069 --> 00:50:28,609
When I wasn't home
and on the second floor.

563
00:50:28,609 --> 00:50:30,949
Twice is a lot between
a man and a woman.

564
00:50:32,479 --> 00:50:34,179
Yeah, whatever.

565
00:50:39,919 --> 00:50:42,619
Did they pay an additional fee?

566
00:50:43,189 --> 00:50:45,659
Stop trying to get a free ride.

567
00:51:05,819 --> 00:51:10,819
<i>(Dressing Room / "Last Goodbye")
(Jeong Ah-ran)</i>

568
00:51:36,479 --> 00:51:37,909
How may I help you?

569
00:51:37,909 --> 00:51:40,379
Are they filming right now?

570
00:51:40,379 --> 00:51:43,719
They're taking a break for the moment.

571
00:51:43,849 --> 00:51:46,249
There's a problem.

572
00:51:46,989 --> 00:51:48,019
A problem?

573
00:51:48,719 --> 00:51:50,389
What do you want?

574
00:51:50,389 --> 00:51:51,589
Oh, I...

575
00:51:52,959 --> 00:51:54,159
Here we go again.

576
00:51:54,159 --> 00:51:55,899
We won't be able to go home tonight.

577
00:52:05,539 --> 00:52:06,509
Director.

578
00:52:06,909 --> 00:52:07,809
Yes?

579
00:52:08,209 --> 00:52:09,809
Cohesive or not,

580
00:52:10,039 --> 00:52:11,849
I can't get beaten up anymore.

581
00:52:12,909 --> 00:52:15,249
I know you're having a hard time,

582
00:52:15,249 --> 00:52:19,989
but your character must seem real.

583
00:52:19,989 --> 00:52:20,989
Real?

584
00:52:21,389 --> 00:52:24,399
If I'm hit this much,
I should be hospitalized.

585
00:52:25,729 --> 00:52:28,259
Last time, my head burst
because I got kicked,

586
00:52:28,259 --> 00:52:29,899
but I didn't go to the hospital.

587
00:52:29,899 --> 00:52:32,499
I ate chicken for my kid's birthday.

588
00:52:32,499 --> 00:52:33,829
I even wore a weird fur hat

589
00:52:33,829 --> 00:52:35,439
and showed them the menu.

590
00:52:36,099 --> 00:52:38,369
I was kicked for several minutes,

591
00:52:38,969 --> 00:52:40,139
but then I cried

592
00:52:40,879 --> 00:52:42,209
and made coffee.

593
00:52:42,479 --> 00:52:44,249
While vowing to live.

594
00:52:47,619 --> 00:52:48,719
Director.

595
00:52:49,249 --> 00:52:50,649
You've never been beaten up, right?

596
00:52:51,149 --> 00:52:52,719
No, I haven't.

597
00:52:54,789 --> 00:52:56,359
Look at me.

598
00:52:58,719 --> 00:53:01,629
If you're hit this much,
you're nearly dead.

599
00:53:02,159 --> 00:53:05,929
Your mouth is so swollen,
you can't swallow.

600
00:53:06,729 --> 00:53:10,139
Your ribs painfully
crush you with each step.

601
00:53:10,939 --> 00:53:14,339
In the morning,
you think you died in your sleep.

602
00:53:17,139 --> 00:53:18,139
But

603
00:53:19,279 --> 00:53:22,679
you still make me
boil water and drink tea.

604
00:53:22,679 --> 00:53:24,199
That's a character set-up?

605
00:53:25,019 --> 00:53:26,849
You know it's product placement.

606
00:53:33,029 --> 00:53:35,199
I'm not saying I don't want to get hit.

607
00:53:36,629 --> 00:53:37,989
I'm not really...

608
00:53:38,499 --> 00:53:40,599
I'm not really getting hit.

609
00:53:40,599 --> 00:53:41,869
I'm just pretending.

610
00:53:41,869 --> 00:53:43,969
So it's not that hard to endure.

611
00:53:45,239 --> 00:53:46,239
But...

612
00:53:46,909 --> 00:53:50,179
getting beaten to a pulp,
then going on with life,

613
00:53:50,949 --> 00:53:52,779
smiling like nothing happened...

614
00:53:54,619 --> 00:53:56,379
I can't do that anymore.

615
00:53:58,249 --> 00:53:59,649
Am I the weird one here?

616
00:54:01,059 --> 00:54:01,819
Huh?

617
00:54:01,819 --> 00:54:05,089
Am I not qualified to act
because of this?

618
00:54:05,859 --> 00:54:06,859
Huh?

619
00:54:09,099 --> 00:54:10,229
Seriously.

620
00:54:21,609 --> 00:54:22,609
Well,

621
00:54:22,879 --> 00:54:24,549
let's eat and film again.

622
00:54:24,649 --> 00:54:26,349
You should go eat, too, Mr. Seo.

623
00:54:26,349 --> 00:54:27,349
Come on.

624
00:54:27,779 --> 00:54:30,319
What's wrong with you?

625
00:54:30,579 --> 00:54:32,289
You know this business.

626
00:54:32,289 --> 00:54:33,789
You're making it tough for others.

627
00:54:35,819 --> 00:54:37,789
Give that to me. I'll drink it.

628
00:54:38,229 --> 00:54:41,959
It doesn't matter who drinks it, right?

629
00:54:41,959 --> 00:54:43,429
Yes, but

630
00:54:43,429 --> 00:54:44,899
let's talk about it later.

631
00:54:44,899 --> 00:54:46,329
I'll drink it.

632
00:54:56,739 --> 00:54:58,129
What are you doing?

633
00:54:58,979 --> 00:55:01,119
Are you on a power trip
because you're the lead?

634
00:55:39,719 --> 00:55:40,919
Let's go home.

635
00:55:46,389 --> 00:55:47,759
Let's go.

636
00:55:53,329 --> 00:55:55,999
No. We have 5 scenes left.

637
00:55:59,169 --> 00:56:00,239
Then...

638
00:56:03,479 --> 00:56:04,709
let's go sit in your car.

639
00:56:49,619 --> 00:56:50,759
Jeong-su!

640
00:56:51,589 --> 00:56:53,589
How about this?

641
00:56:54,129 --> 00:56:55,329
They look nice.

642
00:56:57,869 --> 00:57:00,499
You didn't even look closely enough.

643
00:57:00,499 --> 00:57:02,139
You look pretty in everything.

644
00:57:02,139 --> 00:57:03,999
They're pretty, so buy anything.

645
00:57:19,119 --> 00:57:21,919
How much is this and this?

646
00:57:21,919 --> 00:57:23,719
This is 310,000 won.

647
00:57:23,719 --> 00:57:25,159
And this is 273,000 won.

648
00:57:25,159 --> 00:57:26,189
Oh, my!

649
00:57:26,189 --> 00:57:27,959
Why are they so expensive?

650
00:57:28,359 --> 00:57:30,329
They're not even a designer label.

651
00:57:30,899 --> 00:57:31,969
Jeez.

652
00:57:33,569 --> 00:57:35,499
Come on, Mom.

653
00:57:35,799 --> 00:57:36,899
What?

654
00:57:37,169 --> 00:57:39,739
Be quiet. There are customers here.

655
00:57:40,139 --> 00:57:41,609
I'm a customer, too, you bastard.

656
00:57:41,609 --> 00:57:44,439
Then do whatever you want.

657
00:57:44,439 --> 00:57:45,609
I'm sorry.

658
00:57:45,609 --> 00:57:46,809
It's okay.

659
00:57:48,279 --> 00:57:52,049
With an employee discount
and member discount,

660
00:57:52,049 --> 00:57:53,089
the amount is this.

661
00:57:54,319 --> 00:57:56,719
It's still expensive.

662
00:57:56,719 --> 00:57:58,459
Mom, just get them.

663
00:57:58,459 --> 00:57:59,729
I'll buy them for you.

664
00:57:59,729 --> 00:58:00,529
Here you go.

665
00:58:00,529 --> 00:58:01,629
Thank you.

666
00:58:02,699 --> 00:58:03,959
Just get them?

667
00:58:03,959 --> 00:58:05,329
Just get them.

668
00:58:05,529 --> 00:58:08,269
Look pretty when you're
meeting your friends.

669
00:58:08,269 --> 00:58:09,739
You said you're the oldest.

670
00:58:09,739 --> 00:58:11,369
Wear new shoes at least.

671
00:58:11,369 --> 00:58:14,039
There's always a catch.

672
00:58:14,039 --> 00:58:15,309
- We'll take them.
- Okay.

673
00:58:15,309 --> 00:58:16,779
This size fits you, right?

674
00:58:16,779 --> 00:58:18,279
- Yes.
- Okay.

675
00:58:21,679 --> 00:58:24,919
You know your father-in-law?
Bu-jeong's dad?

676
00:58:24,919 --> 00:58:26,119
What about him?

677
00:58:26,519 --> 00:58:27,519
Did...

678
00:58:27,789 --> 00:58:30,259
he say anything about me?

679
00:58:31,789 --> 00:58:32,859
About you?

680
00:58:32,859 --> 00:58:35,329
About a phone call with me.

681
00:58:35,329 --> 00:58:37,399
Or just about everyday life.

682
00:58:37,399 --> 00:58:39,129
Did you call him?

683
00:58:39,129 --> 00:58:40,269
Oh, well.

684
00:58:40,269 --> 00:58:42,239
We can talk on the phone.

685
00:58:42,239 --> 00:58:46,009
We're in-laws each with
an only child. We're close.

686
00:58:47,879 --> 00:58:49,809
Something's fishy.

687
00:58:50,039 --> 00:58:51,479
You caused some kind of trouble, right?

688
00:58:51,479 --> 00:58:52,809
What do you mean?

689
00:58:52,809 --> 00:58:54,819
I'm not the type to cause trouble.

690
00:58:54,819 --> 00:58:55,919
Look at you.

691
00:58:56,179 --> 00:58:59,319
You're not calling me names.
You did something.

692
00:58:59,319 --> 00:59:00,749
What did you do?

693
00:59:01,219 --> 00:59:02,959
I didn't do anything.

694
00:59:02,959 --> 00:59:04,459
You're making me more suspicious of you.

695
00:59:04,459 --> 00:59:06,889
If I say I didn't do anything, I didn't.

696
00:59:09,329 --> 00:59:12,669
Is everything alright at
Bu-jeong's workplace?

697
00:59:12,829 --> 00:59:13,769
Huh?

698
00:59:14,469 --> 00:59:15,469
Of course.

699
00:59:15,669 --> 00:59:16,769
Why?

700
00:59:16,769 --> 00:59:17,909
What do you mean?

701
00:59:17,909 --> 00:59:21,509
I can ask about
my daughter-in-law's work.

702
00:59:23,539 --> 00:59:26,309
Did you meet Father

703
00:59:26,709 --> 00:59:28,319
because of Bu-jeong?

704
00:59:28,819 --> 00:59:30,549
I didn't meet anyone.

705
00:59:30,549 --> 00:59:31,789
No.

706
00:59:32,289 --> 00:59:33,949
It looks like you did.

707
00:59:36,159 --> 00:59:37,589
- Thank you.
- Here's your card.

708
00:59:37,989 --> 00:59:39,429
Thanks, Son.

